Citation.sTitle: Solubility of D-(p-Hydroxy)phenylglycine in Water + 2-Propanol from (293 to 343) K
Citation.sAbstract: The solubility of D-(p-hydroxy)phenylglycine in binary 2-propanol + water was measured using a synthetic method with a laser-assisted observation of a solute dissolution in the temperature range from (293 to 343) K and mole fraction (x2 o) range of 0.0000 to 0.5451. The results were correlated with a semiempirical equation.
